Included are Law Enforcement arrest cards and correspondence, 1940-1987. The bulk of the arrest cards date from the predecessor Board of Fisheries and Game; Deputy Commissioner, 1975-2006; 
the Governor's Task Force Report on State Beaches and Shoreline Parks, 1975, from the Parks and Recreation Unit; and files from Joseph O. Elmer, 1966-1975. 
Elmer was a senior civil engineer in the Water and Related Resources Unit.
